<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOCIAL SECURITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Robert Kurtz's letter (Dec. 29) suggests he was either misinformed or he 
misunderstood how taxes on Social Security benefits are appropriated.Income 
taxes on Social Security benefits are deposited into the Social Security 
retirement and survivors (OASI) trust fund.  
</P>
<P>
 Taxation of Social Security benefits for some recipients will increase from 
50% to 85% after 1993. Taxes on the increase (35%) are deposited into the 
Medicare trust fund which, combined with the 1.45% Social Security tax (FICA), 
pays for hospital benefits under Medicare. Treatment of taxes resulting from 
the initial 50% will not change after 1993 -- these taxes will continue to be 
deposited into the OASI trust fund.  
</P>
<P>
 WANDA H. WALDMAN 
</P>
<P>
 District Manager 
</P>
<P>
 Social Security Administration 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana 
