<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: JASTREM, WAUGAMAN GIVEN TOP SPOTS AT ACME HOLDINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John F. Jastrem has been promoted to president and chief operating officer of 
Acme Holdings Inc., an equipment rental company based in Irvine, as part of an 
overall management reorganization. Jastrem had been executive vice president 
and chief operating officer since August, 1993.Ira Mendelsohn will continue as 
chairman and chief executive of Acme. Before joining the company, Jastrem was 
senior vice president and chief financial officer of Knapp Communications 
Corp., publisher of Architectural Digest and Bon Appetit magazines, which were 
recently sold to Conde Nast Publications. He was also chief financial officer 
for Reliance Steel & Aluminum Co., a metals distribution company; and part of 
Wickes Cos. management team. In addition, Douglas A. Waugaman has been 
appointed vice president and chief financial officer, succeeding Bruce A. 
Warren, who will serve as a consultant to the company for the next several 
months. Waugaman was previously vice president of finance for Knapp 
Communications Corp. Dan V. Olson has been chosen for the new post of director 
of finance and tax. Olson formerly held positions with Collins and Aikman Group 
Inc., most recently as director of federal and state tax compliance. Larry 
Morrison has been appointed to the newly created post of acting vice president 
of information services. Morrison was previously senior partner of Andersen 
Consulting. And Simon Lu will be joining the company Feb. 2 as director of 
information technology, reporting to Morrison. Lu was formerly in charge of 
computer systems for Conde Nast's West Coast operations. 
</P>
