<P>
 GLENDORA: Superior Court Judge Diane Wayne ordered the city this week to pay 
roughly $24,000 in attorney's fees to the Glendora Preservation Foundation, 
bringing the city's bill for fighting a foundation lawsuit to more than 
$100,000. The foundation successfully sued the city last April over demolition 
of a potentially historic 83-year-old Craftsman bungalow. 
</P>
