<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SANTA MONICA; RUSSIAN IMMIGRANT IS SHOT IN FACE IN APPARENT 
MUGGING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 27-year-old Russian immigrant who may not have understood a mugger's demands 
remained in serious condition Wednesday after being shot in the face during an 
alleged robbery attempt on Ocean Park Boulevard in Santa Monica this week. 
</P>
<P>
 Two men were arrested Sunday morning shortly after the crime when their car 
stopped with engine trouble on the Santa Monica Freeway near Centinela 
Boulevard, said Santa Monica Police Sgt. Gary Gallinot. 
</P>
<P>
 Police say the men robbed a young couple in the parking lot of Norm's 
restaurant at Lincoln Boulevard and Colorado Avenue at 4:05 a.m. and then 
attempted to rob two Russian immigrants in the 700 block of Ocean Park 
Boulevard shortly afterward. 
</P>
<P>
 "The two Russian victims were . . . apparently switching driving duties when 
the suspects approached and said some initial words in Spanish," Gallinot said. 
"When the two in the car did not respond, the driver's window was smashed with 
two shotgun blasts. The driver was hit but managed to slam the car into 
reverse, which led the robbers to flee." 
</P>
<P>
 The driver, Vladimir Sofman, suffered severe facial wounds and was undergoing 
treatment at UCLA Medical Center. His passenger, 26-year-old Yan Yukhtman, was 
unhurt, Gallinot said. Both are Los Angeles residents. 
</P>
<P>
 Luis Armando Prado, 23, and Juan Munoz Ramirez, 21, were booked for attempted 
murder, robbery and attempted robbery after they were identified by three of 
the victims, Gallinot said. Prado and Ramirez are being held on $525,000 bail. 
</P>
