<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PASADENA; CONSTRUCTION BEGINS ON PCC PARKING AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pasadena City College officials broke ground Wednesday on a five-story 
2,064-space parking structure for students. 
</P>
<P>
 The $9.5-million structure at Del Mar Boulevard and Hill Avenue is scheduled 
to open next January.It will increase the number of parking spaces for students 
to 4,700, college officials said.  
</P>
<P>
 Lack of parking at the 26,000-student college, which serves the west San 
Gabriel Valley, has been an issue for at least 20 years, college officials say. 
</P>
<P>
 The structure is not the college's first attempt to work out its parking 
problems. In May the City Council approved a one-year pilot project that allows 
students to park on some surrounding streets with city permits. 
</P>
<P>
 College officials also hope the new structure, equipped with security lights, 
will address safety concerns raised by students after a woman was pulled into a 
car on campus and raped Sept. 23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
