<HEADLINE>
<P>
APPOINTMENT: CLINTON SELECTION CRITICIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What would motivate President Clinton's transportation secretary to appoint a 
professional lobbyist, outspoken on key issues, to assist the Federal Highway 
Administrator? What kind of politics is behind the recent appointment of Evelyn 
Fierro, a longtime vocal opponent to the 710 Freeway extension, to a key 
position within the agency that will decide on the fate of the project? 
</P>
<P>
 My immediate reaction was disgust when I first read of the appointment in the 
Times San Gabriel Valley Section on Sunday, Dec. 26; but disgust turned to 
disbelief after thinking it over for a few hours.One would question the 
political wisdom of such an obvious blunder. 
</P>
<P>
 Congress must urge the President to seek a reversal of the appointment or face 
redress by the constituency. 
</P>
<P>
 HENRY LESOVSKY 
</P>
<P>
 Alhambra  
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
