<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; ENVIRONMENT: NATIONAL PARKS GUIDE AVAILABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The National Park Service's 1994 winter activity guide for the Santa Monica 
Mountains is available free of charge. 
</P>
<P>
 The guide, which outlines talks, hikes and other ranger-led mountain 
activities, is available by calling (818) 597-9192 or writing: Outdoors, Santa 
Monica Mountains National Recreation Area, 30401 Agoura Road, Suite 100, Agoura 
Hills, CA 91301. Arts: Photo Exhibit on Nepalese Culture 
</P>
<P>
 The Shannon White Gallery will exhibit photographs from Kevin Bubriski's 
recently published book "Portrait of Nepal" today through March 5. 
</P>
<P>
 Bubriski spent four years during the 1970s as a Peace Corps volunteer based in 
Nepal. Since then he has spent much of his time photographing the people of the 
Himalayan mountain country. 
</P>
<P>
 The gallery is at 8214 Melrose Ave., Los Angeles. Hours are 11 a.m. to 5 p.m. 
Wednesday through Saturday. Information: (213) 655-5454. Education: School 
District Member to Host Meeting 
</P>
<P>
 Mark Slavkin, the Los Angeles Unified School District board member who 
represents the Westside, will host a town hall meeting Wednesday from 7 to 9 
p.m. at the Brockton Avenue Elementary School library. 
</P>
<P>
 Topics will include the cluster proposal on district organization, an update 
on public school choice, the LEARN reform program and the state budget. Slavkin 
plans to conduct monthly community meetings. Brockton Avenue Elementary is at 
1309 Armacost Ave. Information: (213) 625-6387 or (818) 997-2300, Ext. 6387. 
</P>
</TEXT>
