<TEXT>
<P>
 Top-seeded Pete Sampras, the defending champion, rallied from a mid-match 
slump to defeat Jason Stoltenberg of Australia, 6-1, 4-6, 7-5, and move into 
the quarterfinals of the New South Wales Open at Sydney, Australia. 
</P>
<P>
 Aaron Krickstein upset seventh-seeded Marc Rosset of Switzerland, 6-3, 7-5, in 
a second-round match and was one of five Americans to reach the quarterfinals. 
Also advancing were sixth-seeded Todd Martin and unseeded Ivan Lendl and Richey 
Reneberg. Miscellany 
</P>
<P>
 Franz Heinzer of Switzerland, the downhill World Cup champion, crashed in 
practice at Kitzbuhel, Austria, and suffered a concussion and bruises, injuries 
that might keep him out of Saturday's World Cup race. 
