<HEADLINE>
<P>
J.F. WILLIAMS SHARP IN VICTORY OVER SCHERANDO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 J.F. Williams wore down 4-5 favorite Scherando to win the $55,000 feature by 1 
3/4 lengths Wednesday at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
 Ridden by Kent Desormeaux, J.F. Williams stalked pace-setter Scherando from 
the start of the six-furlong race, made up ground from the quarter pole, took 
the lead inside the 16th pole and quickly drew clear. 
</P>
<P>
 J.F. Williams' time of 1:08 was the second-fastest for six furlongs during the 
current Santa Anita meeting. He carried 116 pounds. 
</P>
