<P>
 The Lynwood Unified School District will have a special election Feb. 15 to 
break a tie between two incumbents seeking reelection. 
</P>
<P>
 Board members Joe T. Battle and Rachel Chavez each received 1,281 votes in the 
Nov. 2 race. Two of the five board seats were on the ballot, but newcomer Laura 
M. Byrd outpolled the two incumbents. Chavez and Battle have continued to 
serve, making it a six-member board since December. 
</P>
<P>
