SEYMOUR LAWRENCE; PUBLISHED 4 NOBEL LAUREATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Seymour Lawrence, 67, a book publisher whose clients included Katherine Anne 
Porter, William Saroyan, Kurt Vonnegut, Frank Conroy and Thomas Berger.In 1969, 
after Vonnegut's publisher had rejected a manuscript, the writer contracted 
with Lawrence to publish "Slaughterhouse Five." Over the years, Lawrence's 
clients came to include four Nobel laureates: Miguel Angel Asturias, Camilo 
Jose Cela, Pablo Neruda and George Seferis. For many years Lawrence remained 
one of the few independent publishers, but mergers and other economic factors 
forced him to join Dell in 1983. Most recently he had been with Houghton 
Mifflin. In Englewood, Fla., of a heart attack. 
