<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSBITES: FEAST TO AID LAGUNA KIDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNE MICHAUD, Anne Michaud is a staff writer for The Times Orange County 
Edition. Fax Newsbites items to (714) 966-7790, or call (714) 966-7898. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Schoolchildren emotionally affected by the Laguna Beach fires will receive an 
assist Sunday from six area restaurants. The restaurants have organized a 
wine-tasting reception and dinner to raise money for counseling services for 
children in the Laguna Beach Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
 The site is Five Feet Restaurant and the neighboring Engman International 
Gallery. Bette Midler and Dustin Hoffman are honorary chairpersons of the 
event, but Midler will not attend and Hoffman is uncertain, according to the 
event spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
 Still, those attending the benefit will find a notable cast of chefs preparing 
the meal: Paul Squicciarini of Sorrento Grille; Ignazio Vincenzo and Antonio 
Romeo of Romeo Cucina; Rick Sedler of Partner's Bistro; Todd Clore of Claes' 
Seafood at the Hotel Laguna, and Bruce Klier of Cedar Creek Inn. 
</P>
<P>
 The reception begins at 4:30 p.m., with seating for dinner at 6. Tickets are 
$150 per person, and all proceeds will be donated toward the creation of a 
counseling center.  
</P>
<P>
 On the menu are appetizers and desserts prepared by each restaurant. Chefs are 
teaming up to prepare other dishes, which include salad and lamb sirloin. 
</P>
<P>
 For reservations, call (714) 494-6811 or (714) 497-7700, Ext. 208. 
</P>
<P>
 328 Glenneyre St. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Pascal Olhats will open his Epicerie on Friday. The retail store is adjacent 
to the French restaurant Pascal and will offer take-out dishes from the 
restaurant's menu, along with wine, imported cheese, gourmet coffee, pastries 
and catering services. Hours are 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. Monday through Saturday, 10 
a.m. to 2 p.m. on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 1000 Bristol St., Newport Beach. (714) 752-0107. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 John Dominis and Sterling Vineyards are pairing up to offer a winemaker dinner 
on Thursday, Jan. 20. Winery representative John Katopodis will attend. The 
five-course dinner will include smoked Norwegian salmon in a cream sauce over 
pasta with a 1990 Chardonnay and roasted Colorado rack of lamb with a 1991 
pinot noir. 
</P>
<P>
 2901 West Coast Highway, Newport Beach. (714) 650-5112. 
</P>
