<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL; USC TO PLAY HOST TO WASHINGTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ninth-ranked USC will play No. 16 Washington in a game matching the Pacific 10 
Conference's two unbeaten women's basketball teams tonight at USC's Lyon 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
 While USC, 9-1 overall and 2-0 in the Pac-10, and Washington (10-1, 2-0) play, 
Washington State (6-5, 1-1) will be playing UCLA (6-5, 1-1) at Pauley 
Pavilion.The USC game begins at 7:30 p.m., the UCLA game at 6:30. 
</P>
<P>
 Washington has won nine in a row, most recently home victories over Stanford 
(78-61) and California (95-60). It was Stanford's largest margin of defeat in 
its last 80 games. 
</P>
<P>
 The Huskies -- who play at UCLA on Saturday at 2 p.m. -- have been led by 
junior Rhonda Smith, who had 15 points and eight rebounds in the rout of 
fifth-ranked Stanford and held the Cardinal's Anita Kaplan to six points, 10.6 
below her average.  
</P>
<P>
 USC, meanwhile, survived close calls last week in Oregon, defeating Oregon 
State, 63-56, last Thursday and beating Oregon, 47-45 on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA lost, 82-77, at Oregon but beat Oregon State, 76-61. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bruins outscored Oregon State, 30-4, over the last 12 minutes at 
Corvallis. During one stretch, UCLA's Natalie Williams scored 13 of UCLA's 24 
points. She finished with 26 points and 13 rebounds. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
