<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP SOCCER PLAYER'S AGE IS QUESTIONED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Francisco Islas, leading scorer for the top-ranked Santa Ana Valley soccer 
team, might miss the rest of the season, pending a claim by Orange High that 
Islas is too old to play high school soccer. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana Valley Coach Adnan Bayati said Orange High has made a complaint to 
the Southern Section and the Santa Ana Valley administration that Islas was 
born in July 1974, which would make him 19 years old. 
</P>
<P>
 Bayati said Islas will soon produce a birth certificate from his native 
country, Mexico, showing that he was born in July 1976. DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
