<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: TECHNOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 IBM Unit Announces Layoffs: Metaphor Inc., a Silicon Valley-based software 
company owned by International Business Machines Corp., said it will lay off 
20% of its employees.The company also said it has promoted its senior vice 
president of products, Chris Grejtak, to president and chief executive. He 
replaces Catherine Y. Selleck, who is retiring after two years at Metaphor and 
36 years with IBM. About 400 people work for Metaphor. The layoffs, which the 
company said are part of a corporate restructuring, will affect the 
administrative, marketing, sales, services and development staffs. 
</P>
