<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRODUCING THE NEXT ITZHAK PERLMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONNIE KOENENN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Here is a sampling of music lessons in the Los Angeles area. A national list 
of certified music teachers and a free brochure, "Choosing a Music Teacher," 
are available from the Music Teachers National Assn., Carew Tower, 441 Vine 
St., Cincinnati, Ohio 45202-2814. Universities 
</P>
<P>
 * Cal State L.A., Saturday Conservatory of Music. Group lessons, theory and 
several orchestras. One year of lessons a prerequisite. $42 for a 10-week 
session. Financial aid and some instruments available. (213) 343-4109. 
</P>
<P>
 * Cal State Northridge, Community Music School. Five youth orchestras for 
students 6-22. Students must have one year of private instruction and bring 
their own instruments. $40 to $125 per semester. (818) 885-3074. Also 
small-group instruction for beginning and intermediate levels. (818) 885-3180.  
</P>
<P>
 * Cal State Long Beach. Saturday program in strings, woodwind, brass for 
beginning and advanced students. Group, individual instruction. $70 to $150 for 
10 weeks. (310) 985-4533 on Saturdays. 
</P>
<P>
 * Cal State Dominguez Hills. Saturday conservatory program. $180 for 11 
private lessons and a recital. Also Orff Schulwerk method for preschoolers, 
utilizing singing, movement and rhyme. $55 for 10 weeks. (310) 516-3543. 
Independent Schools 
</P>
<P>
 * Neighborhood Music Settlement School, 358 South Boyle Ave. $5 private 
lessons in piano, voice, guitar and orchestral instruments. Scholarships. 
Beginners to pre-professionals. (213) 268-0762.  
</P>
<P>
 * Los Angeles Music and Art School, 3630 East 3rd St. Private lessons in all 
instruments and voice. $10 per half-hour. Scholarships. Beginners to 
pre-professionals. (213) 262-7734.  
</P>
<P>
 * Colburn School of Performing Arts, 3131 S. Figueroa. After-school and 
Saturday instruction in full range of band and orchestral instruments. Chamber 
groups, jazz, guitar and string orchestra. Beginners through pre-professionals. 
Private lessons start at $94 a month, classes at $25 a month. Scholarships. 
(213) 743-5252.  
</P>
<P>
 * Pasadena Conservatory of Music, 845 Atchison St. Training in winds, brass, 
strings, keyboards. Individual and group classes from beginning through college 
preparatory. Private lessons, $75 a month; group lessons, $96 for 12-week 
quarter. Scholarships. (818) 798-9426.  
</P>
<P>
 * Evergreen Music Conservatory, 14401 Dickens St., Sherman Oaks. Private 
instruction in piano, guitar, violin, viola, cello, clarinet, flute and 
composition. Beginners through very advanced. $17.50 for a half-hour, $32.50 an 
hour. Financial aid. (818) 501-4869. Methods 
</P>
<P>
 * Suzuki Music Assn. of California, Los Angeles branch. Children 3 and up 
learn by listening, then by reading music. Tuition is approximately $70 to $80 
a month for weekly lessons. More than 100 teachers in the Los Angeles area, for 
piano, violin, viola, cello and flute. (213) 937-6225.  
</P>
<P>
 * Yamaha Music Education Division, Southern California. Keyboard 
group-teaching method with an emphasis on creativity and composition for 
students 4 to adulthood. Tuition is about $60 a month for weekly lessons. For a 
list of local schools, call (800) 722-8856.  
</P>
<P>
 * Piano Mart Rhodes Academy of Music, 11531 Santa Monica Blvd., (310) 
575-9232, or 12023 Victory Blvd., North Hollywood, (818) 753-8080. Piano method 
combining classical and jazz improvisational styles. Private and group 
instruction, $15 to $20 a lesson. Music Stores 
</P>
<P>
 * Marshall Music, 503 Van Ness Ave., Torrance. Seven studios, 15 instructors 
for full range of band and orchestral instruments, piano and guitar. Average 
half-hour lesson is $16. (310) 320-0246 
</P>
<P>
 * McCabe's Guitar Shop, 3101 Pico Blvd., Santa Monica. Twenty-five teachers 
offering lessons in all string instruments. Folk and classical. Beginning to 
advanced. Group classes, $140 for eight weeks. Private lessons, $18 for 
half-hour. (310) 828-4497. 
</P>
<P>
 * Big Valley Music, 8541 Reseda Blvd., Northridge. Six studios for individuals 
and groups. All instruments. Private lessons, $15 a half-hour. (818) 772-1668  
</P>
<P>
 * John Waltrip's Music Center, 1271 S. Baldwin Ave., Arcadia. Private lessons 
and group piano classes. Rental program. Private instruction, $60 a month for a 
half-hour a week. (818) 447-7414, Ext. 130.  
</P>
<P>
 * Thomas Metzler Violin Shop, 604 S. Central Ave., Glendale. Bowed string 
instruments, violin at all levels, rental program. Lessons about $30 an hour. 
(818) 246-0278. 
</P>
<P>
 * Delian Music Systems, 5567 S. Sepulveda, Culver City. Five studios, 
instruction in full range of band and orchestral instruments, keyboard and 
guitar. All levels. Average private lesson is $15. (310) 390-7882. 
</P>
<P>
 * Charles Music Store, 421 N. Glendale Ave., Glendale. Private lessons on most 
band and orchestra instruments. $60 a month for weekly half-hour lessons. (213) 
245-3096. 
</P>
<P>
 * Pedrini Music, 210 N. Brand Blvd., Glendale. Flute, clarinet, saxophone, 
piano and guitar at all levels. About $10 for half-hour lesson. (818) 241-7630. 
</P>
<P>
 * Grayson's Tune Town, 2415 Honolulu Ave., Montrose. Four music studios with a 
dozen teachers. Instrument rentals. Individual lessons, $12.50 for weekly 
half-hour. (818) 249-0993. 
</P>
<P>
 * Spitzer's Valley Arts, 6305 Laurel Canyon, North Hollywood. Studios and five 
teachers for individual instruction in jazz, rock, classical and folk drum and 
guitar. Individual lessons, $14 and up. (818) 763-3383. CONNIE KOENENN 
</P>
