<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: OC HIGH / STUDENT NEWS & VIEWS; GRUNGE ON THE RANGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Youth News Service 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 While grunge fashion has caught on in Orange County, Los Angeles, San 
Francisco and other metro areas, the trend has skipped rural communities such 
as Lake Fallon and Hawthorn, Nev., reports Teen Underground, a newspaper for 
teens in Nevada.Down on the Range Wranglers still rule supreme, reports the 
paper.  
</P>
<P>
 Teens in Fallon say there is less fashion diversity at the local high school 
than in the fashion capitals, in part because there are fewer places to shop. 
"People in Fallon don't know what grunge is," said one teen. "If they do, they 
are considered weird. People here don't spend a lot of money on clothes." 
</P>
