<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; 2ND ARREST MADE IN FALL DRIVE-BY KILLING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A second suspect has been arrested in connection with an October drive-by 
shooting outside a cafe here that killed one man and injured two others, police 
said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Tung Thanh Le, 21, was arrested at his Torrance home Tuesday morning without 
incident, Sgt. Dan Bean said. 
</P>
<P>
 Le is suspected of being in a car that passed by the night of Oct. 20, police 
said.  
</P>
<P>
 Le and several other men are suspected of driving by Cafe Gia Hoi, 9106 
Edinger Ave., and firing on three men who were walking out of the restaurant, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the victims was hit in the neck and foot and fell in front of the cafe 
as patrons and employees ran outside after hearing gunshots. 
</P>
<P>
 The two other victims ran but were followed by the assailants into a 
residential neighborhood on Sweetleaf Street. There, one man was shot in the 
chest and the other in the head. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim with the head wound, Tu Anh Nguyen, 19, of Garden Grove died four 
hours later at Hoag Hospital in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 The survivors have since been released from the hospitals and are recovering, 
Bean said. Their names have not been released to protect them, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Le was being held at the Huntington Beach City Jail in lieu of $250,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
 The first suspect, 27-year-old Phuong Phuc Le of Garden Grove, was arrested 
about a week after the shooting and is being held without bail at the Orange 
County Jail, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The two suspects are not related, Bean said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
