<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; SCHOOL BOUNDARIES MEETINGS PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Westminster School District will hold six informational meetings for 
parents about possible school boundary changes resulting from the reopening of 
Neomia B. Willmore Elementary School. 
</P>
<P>
 The meetings will be during the last week of January and the first week of 
February at several school sites, said spokeswoman Audrey Brown. 
</P>
<P>
 When Willmore reopens in the fall, it will draw 550 children from other nearby 
schools. As a result, the district must balance enrollment at these other 
campuses, including Virginia K. Boos, Ada E. Clegg, Frank N. Eastwood, James W. 
Franklin, C. Fred Schroeder and L.P. Webber elementary schools. 
</P>
<P>
 The Board of Trustees will consider the comments from parents when setting the 
new attendance boundaries. Supt. Gail Wickstrom will make her recommendations 
to the board on Feb. 3. A public hearing on the proposal will be held Feb. 17, 
Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 The district plans to reopen Willmore -- at 7122 Maple St. -- in part because 
hundreds of students who live nearby are now bused to other campuses, Brown 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The meetings will be at 7 p.m. on the following dates and schools: 
</P>
<P>
 * Jan. 24 at Virginia K. Boos Elementary School, 13890 Hammon Place, 
Westminster. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jan. 25 at James W. Franklin Elementary School, 14422 Hammon Lane, 
Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jan. 26 at C. Fred Schroeder Elementary School, 15151 Columbia Lane, 
Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jan. 27 at Ada E. Clegg Elementary and Helen Stacey Intermediate schools, 
6311 Larchwood Drive, Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jan. 31 at Frank N. Eastwood Elementary School, 13552 University St., 
Westminster. 
</P>
<P>
 * Feb. 2 at L.P. Webber Elementary School, 14142 Hoover St., Westminster. 
</P>
<P>
 Spanish and Vietnamese interpreters will be available.JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
