<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; 5 MEN INVADE HOME AND ROB OCCUPANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A couple was robbed of $168,000 worth of computer chips, jewelry, cash and 
guns by five suspected gang members in a home invasion style robbery, police 
said Wednesday. A 21-year-old female family member was raped with a foreign 
object during the takeover, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspects, three of whom were armed with handguns, approached the 
middle-aged couple as they entered their Van Nuys home about 6:30 p.m. Monday 
and occupied the house for five hours, tying up the couple and four other 
family members. Police said they believe the men, identified as being 25 to 30 
years old, were after $50,000 worth of computer chips kept in the house. 
</P>
<P>
 "It appears to be a target robbery," said Officer Russ Wong of the Los Angeles 
Police Department's Asian Crime Investigation Section. "They had an idea of 
what they were looking for."  
</P>
<P>
 Police said they have no suspects in the case. JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</TEXT>
