<P>
 Listings Agreement: Several regional multiple-listing services for home sales 
are expected to announce today in Upland that they have agreed to allow free 
access to each other's listings and will work to set up a common database 
system, a spokesman said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 As a result of the agreement, more than 27,000 listing service members -- the 
majority of which are real estate brokers and brokerages -- will have access to 
nearly 70,000 listings of homes for sale in an area that includes much of 
Orange County: Anaheim, Laguna Beach, Santa Ana, Mission Viejo and San Juan 
Capistrano.While the listing services have not merged, they will share 
information at no cost. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is a good thing for both brokers and home buyers," said Bill Jones, 
chairman of the Southland Area Listings Enterprise, the task force formed to 
develop the expanded access. 
</P>
<P>
 The participating listings services are Multi-Regional Multiple Listing 
Service, which covers the Inland Valley; Orange County Multiple Listing 
Service; Inland Empire West Assn. of Realtors; Pomona Valley Board of Realtors; 
and Redland Board of Realtors. Listing services that cover Newport Beach, Costa 
Mesa and Huntington Beach are not included. 
