<P>
 Building Up Appetites: Birtcher Construction Ltd. in Laguna Niguel recently 
released "The Groundbreaking Gourmet," a collection of recipes collected by the 
Birtcher families and company employees. The 103-page cookbook, which was 
recently distributed to all employees, is now handed out as a corporate 
gift."We decided on a cookbook because we had pot lucks once in awhile and 
several people were always asked to bring the same things because so many 
people liked them," said Julie Majors, an administrative assistant at Birtcher. 
Ron Birtcher, whose grandfather founded the company, contributed the dessert 
recipe for "Drunk Bananas," and the recipe for "Scrambled Eggs Legend," which 
includes ingredients such as caviar and chopped scallions. The book will not be 
available in stores, but employees can purchase extra copies for about $13. 
</P>
</TEXT>
