AROUND THE SOUTH BAY: INGLEWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 RAISING THE FLAG: More than 200 light-pole banners, just like those used in 
the 1984 Olympics, will go up along main thoroughfares in Inglewood next week 
advertising the city's five main claims to fame. 
</P>
<P>
 The yellow-and-white nylon banners will have the business logos of Hollywood 
Park, the Great Western Forum, Inglewood Cemetery and Centinela and Daniel 
Freeman hospitals with the slogan, "City of Champions."  
</P>
<P>
 "It's kind of a mutual enhancement effort," said Assistant City Manager Norman 
Cravens. Partners for Progress, a consortium of the city and the five 
businesses, will pay $21,000 for the banners and city workers will install them 
along Prairie Avenue, the main route from the newly opened Century Freeway into 
the heart of the city. 
</P>
