<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: DEDICATION JAN. 21 FOR SCHOOL CLASSROOMS; EL SEGUNDO; 
DEDICATION TO BE HELD FOR SCHOOL CLASSROOMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Center Street Elementary School in El Segundo will hold a ceremony Jan. 21 to 
dedicate six new portable classrooms -- made possible by the City Council's 
annual gift to the school district of $750,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The prefabricated, air-conditioned classrooms allow the school to reduce the 
average size of its first- and second-grade classrooms from 30 to 25 students, 
Principal Kathy Koop said. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the new portable rooms will house a computer lab. "We had computers," 
Koop said, "but we had them crowded into a half of a classroom. Now, whole 
classes will be able to use the computers at the same time." 
</P>
<P>
 To raise money to fill the lab with new Macintosh computers, the school will 
sponsor a 5-kilometer run Feb. 5. 
